INSERT INTO `oretir_blog_posts` VALUES (1,'5-signs-you-need-new-tires','5 Signs You Need New Tires','5 Señales de que Necesita Llantas Nuevas','<h2>How to Know When It\'s Time for New Tires</h2><p>Your tires are the only part of your car that touches the road, making them one of the most important safety components. Here are 5 signs it\'s time for a replacement:</p><h3>1. Low Tread Depth</h3><p>The penny test is simple: place a penny head-first into the tread. If you can see all of Lincoln\'s head, your tread is too worn. Oregon law requires at least 2/32\" of tread depth.</p><h3>2. Visible Cracks or Bulges</h3><p>Cracks in the sidewall or bulges anywhere on the tire indicate structural damage. These can lead to blowouts and should be addressed immediately.</p><h3>3. Vibration While Driving</h3><p>Unusual vibration could mean uneven wear, misalignment, or internal tire damage. Have it checked — it might be a simple alignment fix or time for new tires.</p><h3>4. Your Tires Are Over 6 Years Old</h3><p>Even with good tread, rubber degrades over time. Most manufacturers recommend replacing tires every 6-10 years, regardless of wear.</p><h3>5. Frequent Loss of Air Pressure</h3><p>If you\'re constantly refilling your tires, there may be a slow leak or the tire bead isn\'t sealing properly. Time for an inspection.</p><p><strong>Need a tire inspection?</strong> Visit Oregon Tires Auto Care at 8536 SE 82nd Ave, Portland, or call (503) 367-9714.</p>','<h2>Cómo Saber Cuándo es Hora de Llantas Nuevas</h2><p>Sus llantas son la única parte de su auto que toca la carretera, haciéndolas uno de los componentes de seguridad más importantes. Aquí hay 5 señales de que es hora de reemplazarlas:</p><h3>1. Profundidad de Banda de Rodadura Baja</h3><p>La prueba del centavo es simple: coloque un centavo de cabeza en la banda. Si puede ver toda la cabeza de Lincoln, la banda está muy desgastada.</p><h3>2. Grietas o Protuberancias Visibles</h3><p>Las grietas en el costado o protuberancias indican daño estructural. Pueden causar reventones y deben atenderse inmediatamente.</p><h3>3. Vibración al Conducir</h3><p>La vibración inusual podría significar desgaste desigual, desalineación o daño interno de la llanta.</p><h3>4. Sus Llantas Tienen Más de 6 Años</h3><p>Incluso con buena banda, el caucho se degrada con el tiempo. La mayoría de fabricantes recomiendan reemplazar cada 6-10 años.</p><h3>5. Pérdida Frecuente de Presión</h3><p>Si constantemente está rellenando sus llantas, puede haber una fuga lenta.</p><p><strong>¿Necesita una inspección?</strong> Visite Oregon Tires Auto Care en 8536 SE 82nd Ave, Portland, o llame al (503) 367-9714.</p>','Don\'t wait until it\'s too late. Learn the warning signs that your tires need replacing.','No espere hasta que sea demasiado tarde. Conozca las señales de advertencia.',NULL,'Oregon Tires',1,'published','5 Signs You Need New Tires | Oregon Tires Auto Care','Learn the 5 warning signs that your tires need replacing. Expert advice from Oregon Tires Auto Care in Portland, OR.','2026-02-22 03:17:43','2026-02-22 03:17:43','2026-02-22 03:17:43'),(2,'why-wheel-alignment-matters','Why Wheel Alignment Matters','Por Qué Importa la Alineación de Ruedas','<h2>The Hidden Cost of Bad Alignment</h2><p>Wheel alignment isn\'t just about driving straight — it affects your tire life, fuel economy, and safety.</p><h3>What is Wheel Alignment?</h3><p>Alignment adjusts the angles of your wheels so they\'re parallel to each other and perpendicular to the ground. Three key angles are adjusted: camber, caster, and toe.</p><h3>Signs of Bad Alignment</h3><p><strong>Pulling to one side:</strong> If your car drifts left or right when you let go of the wheel, your alignment is off.</p><p><strong>Uneven tire wear:</strong> Check your tires — if one side is more worn than the other, alignment is likely the cause.</p><p><strong>Crooked steering wheel:</strong> When driving straight, your steering wheel should be centered.</p><h3>How Often Should You Get Aligned?</h3><p>We recommend checking alignment every 12,000 miles or once a year. Also check after hitting a pothole or curb. Portland roads can be tough on alignment!</p><p><strong>Starting at $75.</strong> <a href=\"/book-appointment?service=wheel-alignment\">Book your alignment today</a>.</p>','<h2>El Costo Oculto de la Mala Alineación</h2><p>La alineación no se trata solo de manejar recto — afecta la vida de sus llantas, economía de combustible y seguridad.</p><h3>¿Qué es la Alineación?</h3><p>La alineación ajusta los ángulos de sus ruedas para que estén paralelas entre sí y perpendiculares al suelo.</p><h3>Señales de Mala Alineación</h3><p><strong>Jalar hacia un lado:</strong> Si su auto se desvía cuando suelta el volante, su alineación está mal.</p><p><strong>Desgaste desigual:</strong> Si un lado de la llanta está más desgastado que el otro.</p><h3>¿Con Qué Frecuencia?</h3><p>Recomendamos verificar cada 12,000 millas o una vez al año.</p><p><strong>Desde $75.</strong> <a href=\"/book-appointment?service=wheel-alignment\">Reserve su alineación hoy</a>.</p>','Proper alignment saves you money on tires and fuel while keeping you safe on the road.','La alineación adecuada le ahorra dinero en llantas y combustible.',NULL,'Oregon Tires',1,'published','Why Wheel Alignment Matters | Oregon Tires Auto Care','Learn why proper wheel alignment saves money and keeps you safe. Expert alignment service in Portland, OR.','2026-02-22 03:17:43','2026-02-22 03:17:43','2026-02-22 03:17:43'),(3,'choosing-tires-for-portland-weather','How to Choose the Right Tires for Portland Weather','Cómo Elegir las Llantas Correctas para el Clima de Portland','<h2>Portland Weather and Your Tires</h2><p>Portland\'s climate is unique — wet, mild winters with occasional snow in the hills, and warm, dry summers. This means your tire choice matters.</p><h3>All-Season vs Winter Tires</h3><p>For most Portland drivers, quality all-season tires are the best choice. They handle rain well and perform adequately in light snow. However, if you commute to the mountains or live in the hills, consider winter tires from November through March.</p><h3>Rain Performance Matters Most</h3><p>With an average of 152 rainy days per year, hydroplaning resistance is crucial. Look for tires with deep grooves and good wet traction ratings. The \"Traction\" grade on the tire label (AA, A, B, C) tells you how well it stops on wet pavement.</p><h3>Our Recommendation</h3><p>We carry a range of new and quality used tires suited for Portland weather. Come in for a free consultation — we\'ll recommend the best option for your vehicle and budget.</p><p><strong>Call (503) 367-9714</strong> or <a href=\"/book-appointment\">book online</a>.</p>','<h2>El Clima de Portland y Sus Llantas</h2><p>El clima de Portland es único — inviernos húmedos y suaves con nieve ocasional en las colinas, y veranos cálidos y secos.</p><h3>Todo Terreno vs Llantas de Invierno</h3><p>Para la mayoría de conductores en Portland, las llantas todo terreno de calidad son la mejor opción.</p><h3>El Rendimiento en Lluvia es lo Más Importante</h3><p>Con un promedio de 152 días lluviosos al año, la resistencia al hidroplaneo es crucial.</p><h3>Nuestra Recomendación</h3><p>Ofrecemos una variedad de llantas nuevas y usadas de calidad. Venga para una consulta gratuita.</p><p><strong>Llame al (503) 367-9714</strong> o <a href=\"/book-appointment\">reserve en línea</a>.</p>','Portland\'s wet winters and mild summers require the right tire strategy. Here\'s what we recommend.','Los inviernos lluviosos de Portland requieren la estrategia correcta de llantas.',NULL,'Oregon Tires',1,'published','Best Tires for Portland Weather | Oregon Tires Auto Care','Expert guide to choosing the right tires for Portland\'s rainy climate. Free consultation at Oregon Tires Auto Care.','2026-02-22 03:17:43','2026-02-22 03:17:43','2026-02-22 03:17:43'),(4,'brake-maintenance-guide','Brake Maintenance: What Every Driver Should Know','Mantenimiento de Frenos: Lo que Todo Conductor Debe Saber','<h2>Don\'t Ignore Your Brakes</h2><p>Brakes are your car\'s most critical safety system. Here\'s what you need to know about keeping them in top condition.</p><h3>Warning Signs</h3><p><strong>Squealing or grinding:</strong> High-pitched squealing usually means brake pads are worn. Grinding means metal-on-metal contact — stop driving and get service immediately.</p><p><strong>Soft or spongy pedal:</strong> If your brake pedal feels soft or goes further than usual, there may be air in the brake lines or a fluid leak.</p><p><strong>Vibration when braking:</strong> This often indicates warped rotors, which can be resurfaced or replaced.</p><h3>How Often to Service Brakes</h3><p>Brake pads typically last 30,000 to 70,000 miles depending on driving style. We recommend inspection every oil change or at least once a year.</p><h3>Brake Service at Oregon Tires</h3><p>We offer complete brake service starting at $100 — pads, rotors, fluid flush, and more. Bilingual service in English and Spanish.</p><p><a href=\"/book-appointment?service=brake-service\"><strong>Book brake service today</strong></a> or call (503) 367-9714.</p>','<h2>No Ignore Sus Frenos</h2><p>Los frenos son el sistema de seguridad más crítico de su auto.</p><h3>Señales de Advertencia</h3><p><strong>Chirridos:</strong> Generalmente significa que las pastillas están desgastadas.</p><p><strong>Pedal suave:</strong> Puede haber aire en las líneas o una fuga de fluido.</p><p><strong>Vibración al frenar:</strong> A menudo indica rotores deformados.</p><h3>Con Qué Frecuencia Servir los Frenos</h3><p>Las pastillas típicamente duran 30,000 a 70,000 millas. Recomendamos inspección al menos una vez al año.</p><p><a href=\"/book-appointment?service=brake-service\"><strong>Reserve servicio de frenos hoy</strong></a> o llame al (503) 367-9714.</p>','Your brakes keep you safe. Learn how to recognize warning signs and when to get service.','Sus frenos lo mantienen seguro. Aprenda a reconocer señales de advertencia.',NULL,'Oregon Tires',1,'published','Brake Maintenance Guide | Oregon Tires Auto Care','Learn brake warning signs and maintenance tips. Professional brake service starting at $100 in Portland, OR.','2026-02-22 03:17:43','2026-02-22 03:17:43','2026-02-22 03:17:43'),(5,'5-signs-your-tires-need-replacing','5 Signs Your Tires Need Replacing','5 Senales de que sus Llantas Necesitan Reemplazo','<h2>How to Know When Your Tires Need Replacing</h2><p>Your tires are the only part of your car that touches the road. Worn tires reduce traction, increase stopping distance, and raise the risk of blowouts. Here are five signs it\'s time for new tires:</p><h3>1. Low Tread Depth</h3><p>The penny test is simple: insert a penny into the tread with Lincoln\'s head facing down. If you can see the top of his head, your tread is below 2/32\" and it\'s time to replace. For Portland\'s rainy conditions, we recommend replacing at 4/32\".</p><h3>2. Uneven Wear Patterns</h3><p>If one side of the tire is more worn than the other, you may have alignment or suspension issues. Get the underlying problem fixed and replace the tires.</p><h3>3. Visible Cracks or Bulges</h3><p>Cracks in the sidewall or bulges on the tire surface indicate structural damage. These tires could fail at any time and should be replaced immediately.</p><h3>4. Vibration While Driving</h3><p>Excessive vibration can indicate internal tire damage, uneven wear, or balance issues. Have it inspected right away.</p><h3>5. Age (6+ Years)</h3><p>Even tires with good tread should be replaced after 6-10 years. Rubber degrades over time regardless of use. Check the DOT code on the sidewall for the manufacture date.</p><p><strong>Need new tires?</strong> Oregon Tires carries a wide selection of new and quality used tires, with professional installation starting at $20 per tire.</p>','<h2>Como Saber Cuando sus Llantas Necesitan Reemplazo</h2><p>Sus llantas son la unica parte de su auto que toca el camino. Las llantas desgastadas reducen la traccion, aumentan la distancia de frenado y elevan el riesgo de reventones. Aqui hay cinco senales de que es hora de llantas nuevas:</p><h3>1. Profundidad Baja del Dibujo</h3><p>La prueba de la moneda es simple: inserte una moneda en el dibujo. Si puede ver la parte superior, el dibujo esta por debajo de 2/32\" y es hora de reemplazar. Para las condiciones lluviosas de Portland, recomendamos reemplazar a 4/32\".</p><h3>2. Patrones de Desgaste Desiguales</h3><p>Si un lado de la llanta esta mas desgastado que el otro, puede tener problemas de alineacion o suspension.</p><h3>3. Grietas o Protuberancias Visibles</h3><p>Las grietas en la pared lateral o protuberancias en la superficie indican dano estructural. Estas llantas deben reemplazarse de inmediato.</p><h3>4. Vibracion al Conducir</h3><p>La vibracion excesiva puede indicar dano interno, desgaste desigual o problemas de balanceo.</p><h3>5. Antiguedad (6+ Anos)</h3><p>Incluso las llantas con buen dibujo deben reemplazarse despues de 6-10 anos. El caucho se degrada con el tiempo.</p><p><strong>Necesita llantas nuevas?</strong> Oregon Tires tiene una amplia seleccion con instalacion desde $20 por llanta.</p>','Learn the warning signs that indicate it\'s time for new tires. Don\'t risk your safety — know when to replace.','Aprenda las senales de advertencia que indican que es hora de llantas nuevas. No arriesgue su seguridad.',NULL,'Oregon Tires',NULL,'published',NULL,NULL,'2026-02-15 10:00:00','2026-02-27 19:04:55','2026-02-27 19:04:55'),(6,'best-tires-portland-wet-weather','Best Tires for Portland\'s Wet Weather','Las Mejores Llantas para el Clima Lluvioso de Portland','<h2>Choosing the Right Tires for Portland Rain</h2><p>With an average of 154 rainy days per year, Portland drivers need tires that perform well in wet conditions. Here\'s what to look for:</p><h3>All-Season vs Rain Tires</h3><p>All-season tires work well for most Portland drivers. They handle wet roads, light snow, and dry pavement. For maximum wet grip, dedicated rain tires or touring tires with high wet traction ratings are the best choice.</p><h3>Key Features for Wet Weather</h3><ul><li><strong>Deep tread grooves</strong> — channels water away from the contact patch</li><li><strong>Siping</strong> — tiny slits in the tread blocks grip wet surfaces</li><li><strong>Silica compound</strong> — modern tire compounds grip better when cold and wet</li><li><strong>High UTQG traction rating</strong> — look for AA or A ratings</li></ul><h3>Tire Brands We Recommend</h3><p>At Oregon Tires, we carry quality brands suited for Pacific Northwest weather. Our team can recommend the best option for your vehicle type, driving style, and budget.</p><h3>Don\'t Forget Tread Depth</h3><p>New tires have 10/32\" of tread. For Portland\'s rainy conditions, we strongly recommend replacing tires at 4/32\" rather than the legal minimum of 2/32\". That extra tread makes a significant difference in wet braking distance.</p><p><strong>Visit us</strong> for a free tire consultation and find the perfect tires for Portland weather.</p>','<h2>Eligiendo las Llantas Correctas para la Lluvia de Portland</h2><p>Con un promedio de 154 dias lluviosos al ano, los conductores de Portland necesitan llantas que funcionen bien en condiciones humedas.</p><h3>Toda Temporada vs Llantas para Lluvia</h3><p>Las llantas para toda temporada funcionan bien para la mayoria. Para maximo agarre en mojado, las llantas de turismo con alta calificacion de traccion son la mejor opcion.</p><h3>Caracteristicas Clave</h3><ul><li><strong>Ranuras profundas</strong> — canalizan el agua</li><li><strong>Siping</strong> — pequenas hendiduras que agarran superficies mojadas</li><li><strong>Compuesto de silice</strong> — mejor agarre en frio y mojado</li><li><strong>Alta calificacion UTQG</strong> — busque AA o A</li></ul><h3>No Olvide la Profundidad del Dibujo</h3><p>Para las condiciones de Portland, recomendamos reemplazar llantas a 4/32\" en lugar del minimo legal de 2/32\".</p><p><strong>Visitenos</strong> para una consulta gratuita de llantas.</p>','Portland gets 43 inches of rain per year. Here\'s how to choose tires that keep you safe on wet roads.','Portland recibe 43 pulgadas de lluvia al ano. Asi es como elegir llantas que lo mantengan seguro en caminos mojados.',NULL,'Oregon Tires',NULL,'published',NULL,NULL,'2026-02-05 10:00:00','2026-02-27 19:04:55','2026-02-27 19:04:55'),(7,'how-often-change-oil','How Often Should You Change Your Oil?','Con Que Frecuencia Debe Cambiar su Aceite?','<h2>Modern Oil Change Intervals</h2><p>The old advice of changing your oil every 3,000 miles is outdated for most vehicles. Modern engines and synthetic oils have extended safe intervals significantly.</p><h3>General Guidelines</h3><ul><li><strong>Conventional oil</strong>: Every 3,000-5,000 miles</li><li><strong>Synthetic blend</strong>: Every 5,000-7,500 miles</li><li><strong>Full synthetic</strong>: Every 7,500-10,000 miles</li></ul><p>Always check your owner\'s manual for the manufacturer\'s recommendation.</p><h3>Factors That Shorten Intervals</h3><ul><li>Frequent short trips (under 10 miles)</li><li>Stop-and-go city driving</li><li>Towing or hauling heavy loads</li><li>Extreme temperatures</li><li>Dusty conditions</li></ul><h3>What Happens If You Wait Too Long?</h3><p>Old oil breaks down, loses viscosity, and fails to protect engine components. This leads to increased friction, overheating, sludge buildup, and eventually expensive engine damage.</p><h3>What\'s Included in Our Oil Change?</h3><p>Every oil change at Oregon Tires includes a new oil filter, fluid level check and top-off, tire pressure check, and a visual multi-point inspection — all starting at just $35.</p>','<h2>Intervalos Modernos de Cambio de Aceite</h2><p>El viejo consejo de cambiar aceite cada 3,000 millas esta desactualizado para la mayoria de los vehiculos.</p><h3>Guia General</h3><ul><li><strong>Aceite convencional</strong>: Cada 3,000-5,000 millas</li><li><strong>Mezcla sintetica</strong>: Cada 5,000-7,500 millas</li><li><strong>Sintetico completo</strong>: Cada 7,500-10,000 millas</li></ul><h3>Factores que Acortan Intervalos</h3><ul><li>Viajes cortos frecuentes</li><li>Conduccion en ciudad</li><li>Remolque o cargas pesadas</li><li>Temperaturas extremas</li></ul><h3>Que Incluye Nuestro Cambio de Aceite?</h3><p>Cada cambio incluye filtro nuevo, revision de fluidos, presion de llantas e inspeccion visual — desde solo $35.</p>','The old 3,000-mile rule is outdated. Learn the modern oil change intervals for your vehicle.','La regla de las 3,000 millas esta desactualizada. Conozca los intervalos modernos de cambio de aceite.',NULL,'Oregon Tires',NULL,'published',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-28 10:00:00','2026-02-27 19:04:55','2026-02-27 19:04:55'),(8,'brake-warning-signs','Brake Warning Signs Every Driver Should Know','Senales de Advertencia de Frenos que Todo Conductor Debe Conocer','<h2>Know Your Brake Warning Signs</h2><p>Your brakes are your vehicle\'s most important safety system. Catching problems early can save you money and prevent dangerous situations on the road.</p><h3>1. Squealing or Squeaking</h3><p>Most brake pads have built-in wear indicators — small metal tabs that contact the rotor when pads are low. That high-pitched squeal is your brakes telling you it\'s time for new pads.</p><h3>2. Grinding Sound</h3><p>If squealing progresses to grinding, the pads are completely worn and metal is contacting metal. This damages your rotors and dramatically increases repair costs. Don\'t wait.</p><h3>3. Pulsating Brake Pedal</h3><p>A pulsating or vibrating brake pedal usually indicates warped rotors. This happens from excessive heat buildup, often from aggressive braking or prolonged braking downhill.</p><h3>4. Soft or Spongy Pedal</h3><p>If the brake pedal feels soft or sinks to the floor, you may have air in the brake lines or a brake fluid leak. This is a serious safety concern — have it inspected immediately.</p><h3>5. Warning Light</h3><p>The brake warning light on your dashboard could indicate low brake fluid, worn pads (on vehicles with sensors), or an ABS system issue. Never ignore it.</p><h3>6. Pulling to One Side</h3><p>If your car pulls when braking, you may have a stuck caliper, uneven pad wear, or a brake hose issue.</p><p><strong>Brake inspection at Oregon Tires</strong> starts at just $100 and includes a full assessment of pads, rotors, calipers, lines, and fluid condition.</p>','<h2>Conozca las Senales de Advertencia de sus Frenos</h2><p>Sus frenos son el sistema de seguridad mas importante de su vehiculo.</p><h3>1. Chirrido</h3><p>La mayoria de las pastillas tienen indicadores de desgaste que producen un sonido agudo cuando estan bajas.</p><h3>2. Sonido de Molienda</h3><p>Si el chirrido progresa a molienda, las pastillas estan completamente desgastadas y metal contacta metal.</p><h3>3. Pedal Pulsante</h3><p>Un pedal pulsante generalmente indica rotores alabeados por acumulacion excesiva de calor.</p><h3>4. Pedal Suave o Esponjoso</h3><p>Si el pedal se siente suave, puede tener aire en las lineas o una fuga de liquido de frenos.</p><h3>5. Luz de Advertencia</h3><p>La luz de frenos puede indicar liquido bajo, pastillas desgastadas o un problema del sistema ABS.</p><h3>6. Jalon hacia un Lado</h3><p>Si su auto se desvia al frenar, puede tener un caliper atascado o desgaste desigual.</p><p><strong>La inspeccion de frenos en Oregon Tires</strong> comienza desde $100 e incluye evaluacion completa.</p>','Don\'t ignore these brake warning signs. Early detection prevents costly repairs and keeps you safe.','No ignore estas senales de advertencia de frenos. La deteccion temprana previene reparaciones costosas.',NULL,'Oregon Tires',NULL,'published',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-20 10:00:00','2026-02-27 19:04:55','2026-02-27 19:04:55');
